@node "ALTSPAM" "AltSpam"
                     @{b}@{u}What is AltSpam?@{ub}@{uu}

Even with the help of TASC.thor there are going to be complaints that bounce
back to you, especially if you complain using IP addresses. AltSpam has 3
main goals:

@{b}1. @{ub} It parses the bounce message (as long as it's reasonably standard) &
    lets you flag the original address as one that should be redirected to
    an address suggested by the bounce message or as completely
    Undeliverable. To supplement the addresses given in the bounce message
    AltSpam will check your traceroute database for entries referring to the
    failed address.
    In case of reply like "we can't or we don't want to do anything..." you
    can now save the FROM address as Undeliverable... :-(
    In case of positive reply but in the message you see an address
    different from the FROM one you can now manually type this address
    instead of using GoodDomain and then edit the db file!

@{b}2. @{ub} It gives you the option to remail the complaint, this time to an address
    more likely to succeed.

@{b}3. @{ub} It gives you the option to send a traceroute request to verify the
    existance of a domain. This will also tell you who provides access to
    the spamming domain, allowing you to complain to them about the original
    domain if you need to.
@endnode

