@node "tr" "TRACEROUTE"

 To get this to work you will find that a script triggered by going online &
another for when you go offline makes life a lot easier:

@{u}Beware: the guide editor used is reformatting the script so usually the "end"
command is not in the right line!! :-(((@{uu}

@{b}Online @{ub} DOS script: execute {path & name of tracetmp}

Arexx:  /* After we go online*/

if open(T,'env:thor/BBSDataPath') then do
   BBSP=READLN(T)
   call close(T)
  end
  else do
   say "Unable to find/read env:thor/BBSdataPath"
   exit end

if open(cfg,'Env:thor/TASC.cfg',r) then do

   do until eof(cfg)
      lin=readln(cfg)
      parse var lin id ':' V
      V=strip(V)

      if upper(left(id,8))='TRACETMP' then
          tracetmp=V
   end

   call close(cfg)
  end
  else do
   tracetmp='trace.tmp' end

if exists(BBSP||'db/'||tracetmp) then do
    address command
    'execute '||BBSP||'db/'||tracetmp
    'echo "Finished" > env:thor/traced' end


@{b}Offline @{ub} DOS: rename {name & path of traceroute database} {name & path of
traceroute database}.old tail -[number of lines to keep] {name & path of
traceroute database}.old {name & path of traceroute database} delete {name &
path of traceroute database}.old  quiet

ARexx: /* After we go offline*/

if open(T,'env:thor/BBSDataPath') then do
   BBSP=READLN(T)
   call close(T)
  end
  else do
   say "Unable to find/read env:thor/BBSdataPath"
   exit end

BBSP=BBSP||'db/'

if open(cfg,'Env:thor/TASC.cfg',r) then do

   do until eof(cfg)
      lin=readln(cfg)
      parse var lin id ':' V
      V=strip(V)

      if upper(left(id,8))='TRACETMP' then
          tracetmp=V

      if upper(left(id,7))='TRACEFI' then
          tracefi=V

      if upper(left(id,8))='TRACELEN' then
          tracelen=V
   end

   call close(cfg)
  end
  else do
   tracetmp='trace.tmp'
   tracefi='spamtrace.db'
   tracelen='3000' end

address command /* Delete the old temporary file? */

if exists('env:thor/traced') then
    'delete '||BBSP||tracetmp' >nil:'

/* Shorten the traceroute database */

if exists(BBSP||tracefi) then do
    'rename '||bbsp||tracefi||' '||bbsp||tracefi'.old'
    'tail -'||tracelen||' '||bbsp||tracefi'.old >' bbsp||tracefi
    'delete '||bbsp||tracefi'.old  quiet' end

exit
@endnode

@node "History" "History"

          @{b}@{u}TASC.thor@{ub}@{uu} What's been added since 1.6?


31 Jan 2000 : 002.003 : Added support for "X-Report"

23 Jan 2000 : 002.002 : Added "LockGUI", a must for long messages... :-|
                        To avoid unwanted "deadlock" the needed "signal on"
                        routines have been created

22 Jan 2000 : 002.001 : revorked again the IP checking in "boss" &
                        "fakeboss"
                        Removed final '>' in reply-to if present

19 Jan 2000 : 002.000 : Cleaned up the code and reworked a bit the guide
                        Moved spamaddr to "db/" for consistency
                        Added switch @{"SkipName" link "CONFIG" 27}
                        Corrected the "path:" header handling
                        Corrected the "NNTP" header handling if "Date" is
                        there...
                        Corrected the IP discovery in "parent of..."
                        Added "X-Complaints-to:" search in header

o   Headers are now checked for lines containing 'sender' & this is parsed
    to give another potential address

o   Text searching (optional) looking for both http & email addresses.

o   Parsing of the Received: line has been rewritten to streamline it a bit.

o   Traceroute requester (Optional) to make the spam.db more effective at
    locating the correct addresses.

o   Recognition of 'Faked' as an entry in spam.db, allowing TASC to parse
    the preceeding Received: line for addresses.


         @{b}@{u}AltSpam.thor@{ub}@{uu} What's been added since 0.4?

23 Jan 2000 : 002.002 : Added "LockGUI", a must for long messages... :-|
                        To avoid unwanted "deadlock" the needed "signal on"
                        routines have been created
                        Added "From" for those domain which is not worth
                        complaining :-(
                        you should add these as "undeliverable"...
                        Added the option to manually type a new address

22 Jan 2000 : 002.001 : corrected extraction of addresses (removed final
                        '>')

19 Jan 2000 : 002.000 : Cleaned up the code

o   Recognition for the 'Faked' entry in spam.db

o   Can now add  entries as 'Faked' to spam.db via another list option.

o   Can now request a traceroute to any of the addresses parsed.

o   Now reads the traceroute database to help avoid further bounces


                      @{b}@{u}Gooddomain.thor@{ub}@{uu}

23 Jan 2000 : 002.002 : ...just bumped up the version...

22 Jan 2000 : 002.001 : ...just bumped up the version...

19 Jan 2000 : 002.000 : Cleaned up the code

I knocked this together quickly to grab the domain of a favourable response &
add a recognition entry to spam.db. Error checking is pretty minimal, but it
seems fine here.

                         @{b}@{u}spamaddr@{ub}@{uu}

For the Italian users I've added the Italian Naming Authority.
@endnode

